<head>REFUTE</head><list type="altnames">
<item>DISPROVE</item>
<item>PROVE WRONG</item>
<item>PROVE FALSE</item>
<item>DEBUNK</item>
<item>DISCREDIT</item>
<item>INVALIDATE</item>
<item>INFORMAL POKE HOLES IN</item>
<item>FORMAL CONFUTE</item></list><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">反駁</item><item xml:lang="och">難na4n</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PROVE that something is NOT TRUE.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There is no current and common word for refutation. The closest one can come is nàn 難 "make objections" and fēi 非 "declare to be wrong".</p>
<p>NB: Bó 駁 is post-Buddhist.</p></div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>批駁</p>
<p>駁斥</p>
<p>駁倒</p>
<p>反駁</p>
<p>駁</p>
<p>批判</p>
<p>批</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p></div></div>
